contentHtml: #51. What's the output? function getInfo(member, year) { member.name = 'Lydia'; year = '1998'; } const person = { name: 'Sarah' }; const birthYear = '1997'; getInfo(person, birthYear); console.log(person, birthYear); javascript A: { name: "Lydia" }, "1997" B: { name: "Sarah" }, "1998" C: { name: "Lydia" }, "1998" D: { name: "Sarah" }, "1997" Answer Answer: A Argument
